* Problem:
recv_all(vector<char>, size) called on socket without size B causes problems when timeout enabled.
Internal recv throws timeout exception, which bypasses resize operation in recv_all.
This causes vector to have wrong size upon return.

Not able to catch exception in recv_all(vector) because number of bytes actually received would be lost.
Catching exception in recv_all(void*) causes problems. Can't return number of bytes AND throw exception.

* Redesign and clean up string interface.

* Test vector<> with other types beyond char.

* Add UDP support.

